</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C354656399451124FF36FCA7FDB9FC46" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BF136E899451124FF36FCA7FDB9FC46" blockId="68.[124,653,193,920]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">ETYMOLOGY: The specific epithet is a Latin adjective meaning ‘‘stretch out’’. I refer to the extended condition of the posterior patch of the elytral middiscal setal tuft.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
